{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\n**Cut the reconciler over** to the self-healing ref-lock (C1+C2), behind an expand-contract switch\nso the file backend is retained for rollback. No band-aids are removed here (that is C4).\n\n**Depends on: 524d-00fa-66ef-4432 (C1), 7522-129b-1380-418c (C2).** `_ref_lock`/`renew()` are\ndelivered by C1/C2 and must be merged first.\n\n- Add a `[reconciler] lock_backend = file | ref` config key (`_config_schema.py`). Default stays\n  `file`; `ref` selects the new path. This is the rollback lever.\n- Rewire `acquire_pass_lock`/`release_pass_lock` and the phase-gate in `_advisory_lock.py:243,302,\n  69-70` so that under `lock_backend=ref` they use `_ref_lock` on `refs/reconciler/lock` and\n  `refs/reconciler/gate` instead of `_write_file_to_tickets_branch`. **Fully specify the\n  `refs/reconciler/gate` lifecycle:** who creates it, its blob (same schema as the lock), how phase\n  transitions CAS-update it, and consumer behavior — it is CAS-managed, not operator-freeform.\n- **`acquire_pass_lock` failure contract:** when the create-only CAS is rejected (someone holds it),\n  raise `ReconcileLockError` (matching today's file-lock \"already held\" semantics) rather than an\n  opaque `CalledProcessError`.\n- Update `rebar_reconciler/__main__.py:373-447` (Steps 2a/2b/3) to acquire, start the C2 daemon-thread\n  heartbeat (`renew()` at `max(1, lease//3)`), and release in a `finally`. **Concrete lost-lease\n  abort mechanism:** acquire creates a `threading.Event` (`lock_lost`); the heartbeat daemon, on\n  `LeaseLostError` from `renew()`, calls `lock_lost.set()` and exits (a daemon thread cannot raise\n  into the main thread). The main pass **polls `lock_lost.is_set()` at defined checkpoints** (each\n  per-ticket iteration in the reconcile loop) and, if set, raises `ReconcileLockLost` to abort the\n  pass cleanly (the `finally` release is then a no-op — the lock is already gone). Idempotent ->\n  safe re-run. Thread the acquire handle/oid through acquire -> renew -> release.\n- Under `lock_backend=ref`, stop writing `.reconciler-pass-lock`/`.reconciler-phase-gate` to the\n  tickets tree. Authoritative ref on `origin`; acquire/renew/release push via\n  `--force-with-lease=<ref>:<old>` (explicit lease ref form, never bare).\n- **Edit set also includes the external consumers** that name the file locks:\n  `.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml` (must fetch `refs/reconciler/*` before acquire),\n  `docs/architecture.md`, and `docs/concurrency.md` (update the I6 file-lock exception note). Update\n  the existing file-lock tests `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/state/test_advisory_lock.py` and\n  `test_advisory_lock_cas_race.py` to cover the ref backend.\n\nScope note: `merge=ours`/`.gitattributes`, the `b859` retry loop, and the file-lock code are LEFT IN\nPLACE here (removed in C4) so this change is independently bisectable and reversible via the flag.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A `[reconciler] lock_backend` key selects `file` (default) or `ref`; under `ref`,\n      `acquire_pass_lock`/`release_pass_lock` + phase-gate use `_ref_lock` over `refs/reconciler/*`\n      and no `.reconciler-*` file is written to the tickets branch.\n- [ ] The `refs/reconciler/gate` lifecycle is fully specified and CAS-managed (creation, blob format,\n      atomic phase transition, consumer); `acquire_pass_lock` raises `ReconcileLockError` on a\n      rejected CAS, not a raw subprocess error.\n- [ ] `__main__.py` acquires, heartbeats at ~lease/3 via the daemon thread, releases in `finally`, and\n      aborts the pass on a lost-lease signal; a crashed pass (no release) is reclaimable after lease\n      expiry (test with a short configured lease).\n- [ ] `.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml` fetches `refs/reconciler/*` before acquire; the\n      `refs/reconciler/*` push uses explicit `--force-with-lease=<ref>:<old>`; `docs/architecture.md`\n      + `docs/concurrency.md` (I6) updated.\n- [ ] Lost-lease abort is a `threading.Event` (`lock_lost`) set by the heartbeat daemon and polled\n      at per-ticket checkpoints in the reconcile loop; on set the pass raises `ReconcileLockLost` and\n      the `finally` release no-ops (test: heartbeat loses lease mid-pass -> pass aborts, no double-run).\n- [ ] Idempotency asserted by a named double-acquire convergence test; existing file-lock tests\n      (`test_advisory_lock.py`, `test_advisory_lock_cas_race.py`) extended for the ref backend.\n      Non-integration suite green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783223831761492001,"uuid":"4cfd12fa-41ab-4330-b23e-1b818981b2a1"}